## Example Usage

### Importing and managing an existing user

```hcl
# First, import the user:
# terraform import axual_user.john b21cf1d63a55436391463cee3f56e393

resource "axual_user" "john" {
  first_name    = "John"
  last_name     = "Doe"
  email_address = "john.doe@example.com"
  phone_number  = "+37253412551"
  roles         = [
    { name = "APPLICATION_AUTHOR" },
    { name = "ENVIRONMENT_AUTHOR" },
    { name = "STREAM_AUTHOR" }
  ]
}
```

### Referencing a user via data source (recommended)

```hcl
data "axual_user" "john" {
  email_address = "john.doe@example.com"
}

# Use data.axual_user.john.id to reference the user
```

For a full example which shows the capabilities of the latest Terraform provider, check https://github.com/Axual/terraform-provider-axual/tree/master/examples/axual.

## Import

Import is supported using the following syntax:

```shell
terraform import axual_user.<LOCAL NAME> <USER UID>
terraform import axual_user.test_user b21cf1d63a55436391463cee3f56e393
```